The execution phase of the block. Stores the `spec_version` and `spec_name` of when the last runtime upgrade happened. Mapping between a topic (represented by T::Hash) and a vector of indexes of events in the `<Events<T>>` list. All topic vectors have deterministic storage locations depending on the topic. This allows light-clients to leverage the changes trie storage tracking mechanism and in case of changes fetch the list of events of interest. The value has the type `(T::BlockNumber, EventIndex)` because if we used only just the `EventIndex` then in case if the topic has the same contents on the next block no notification will be triggered thus the event might be lost. Allows block producers to claim a small reward for evicting a contract. If a block producer fails to do so, a regular users will be allowed to claim the reward. If contract is not evicted as a result of this call, no actions are taken and the sender is not eligible for the reward.destaux_senderOption<T::AccountId> Instantiates a new contract from the `codehash` generated by `put_code`, optionally transferring some balance. Instantiation is executed as follows: - The destination address is computed based on the sender and hash of the code. - The smart-contract account is created at the computed address. - The `ctor_code` is executed in the context of the newly-created account. Buffer returned   after the execution is saved as the `code` of the account. That code will be invoked   upon any call received by this account. - The contract is initialized. Makes a call to an account, optionally transferring some balance. * If the account is a smart-contract account, the associated code will be executed and any value will be transferred. * If the account is a regular account, any value will be transferred. * If no account exists and the call value is not less than `existential_deposit`, a regular account will be created and any value will be transferred.<T::Lookup as StaticLookup>::Sourcevalue Stores the given binary Wasm code into the chain\'s storage and returns its `codehash`.
